text: Saint-Thégonnec Loc-Eguiner () is a commune. It is found in the region Brittany in the Finistère department in the northwest of France. The municipality was created on 1 January 2016 and consists of the former communes of Saint-Thégonnec (the seat) and Loc-Eguiner-Saint-Thégonnec.Arrêté préfectoral 23 December 2015 == References == Category:2016 establishments in France Category:Communes in Finistère
title: Saint-Thégonnec Loc-Eguiner
